The paper deals with the problem of head and human detection using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves designing a head-body relationship discriminating module, which involves learning relationships between heads and human bodies, and leveraging this learned relationship to improve detection performance. This involves the use of machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method also involves reducing false positives, which is a common problem in object detection, and involves optimization techniques that fall under the category of robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper involves experiments on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
